  "pages": [
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "text": "With budding blocks in mind you designed the Crystallarieum: an Ink-powered contraption that grows chunks of raw ore into sparkling crystals. Though your best efforts failed to grow actual $(l:general/shards)gems$(/l), you quickly realised that it could grow all sorts of other resources instead.$(br2)Throw raw ore on top to let it crystallize into a Bud, able to be grown."
    },
    {
      "type": "spectrum:pedestal_crafting",
      "title": "Pedestal Recipe",
      "recipe": "spectrum:pedestal/tier4/crystallarieum",
      "text": "$(br)Growing resources requires:$(li)a Catalyst$(li)one color of Ink, supplied via $(l:magic/ink_flask)Flask$()"
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "title": "Catalysts",
      "text": "Each catalyst has a different effect on bud growth:$(br)while one catalyst may reduce the required amount of ink, another may alter the duration of the process.."
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "title": "Metals vs. Crystals",
      "text": "$(thing)Metallic resources$() require unrefined materials such as $(item)Raw Iron$(), resulting in a $(item)Small Iron Bud$() that will grow steadily until it can be safely harvested.$(br2)For $(thing)crystalline resources$(), an existing crystal can be used as a seed to grow identical copies of itself."
    },
